<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-27T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-27T22:00:00-05:00" n="428" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d428">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/6253:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-28T05:00:00+02:00">October 28, 1940—5 a.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received October 28—3:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>262. Following some more absurd Italian news agency charges of
                                    Greek armed action in Albania, fully denied by the Greek
                                    Government yesterday, the Italian Minister handed the Premier an
                                    ultimatum at 3 o’clock this morning to [expire?] at 6, demanding
                                    permission to occupy certain strategic points. When the Premier
                                    asked what points, the Minister said he did not know. This last
                                    I have from the British Minister who was at once called in
                                    consultation. Indications are that Greece will not comply.
                                    Athens is already blacked out.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>